"'''This Time Around'''" is a song by American recording artist and song-writer [[Michael Jackson]] that features the vocals from rapper [[The Notorious B.I.G.]]. The song appears on Jackson's ninth studio album, entitled ''[[HIStory: Past, Present and Future, Book I]]'', which was released in 1995 as a two-disc set. "This Time Around" was written by Jackson, [[Dallas Austin]], [[The Notorious B.I.G.|Christopher Wallace]], [[Bruce Swedien]] and [[Rene Moore]]; Jackson, Austin, Swedien and Moore also serve as producers to the song. The song's lyrics details both musicians problems with being famous and stardom. 

In December 1995, the track was released as a [[promotional recording|promotional single]] in the United States only, containing a radio edit and remixes. "This Time Around" had a good chart performance, having charted solely due to radio airplay throughout the country.  The song peaked at number eighteen, twenty-three and thirty-six on ''Billboard''{{'}}s  and Dance Music/Club Play Singles, [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] and Rhythmic Top 40 music charts. "This Time Around" received generally mixed to positive reviews from contemporary music critics.

== Background and composition ==
{{Listen|pos=left |title = "This Time Around" |description = A twenty-five second long audio sample of "This Time Around". |filename = Michael Jackson - This Time Around.ogg}}
"This Time Around" is a song by American recording artist [[Michael Jackson]] that features vocals rapper [[The Notorious B.I.G.]]. The song was recorded by both musicians in 1994 and 1995 for Jackson's ninth studio album, entitled ''[[HIStory: Past, Present and Future, Book I]]'', which was released in 1995 as a two-disc set.<ref name="linernotes">''[[HIStory: Past, Present and Future, Book I]]'' liner notes [[Epic Records]] (1995).</ref> "This Time Around" was written by Jackson, [[Dallas Austin]], [[The Notorious B.I.G.|Christopher Wallace]], [[Bruce Swedien]] and [[Rene Moore]]; Jackson, Austin, Swedien and Moore also serve as producers to the song.<ref name="linernotes"/> 

"This Time Around" is credited as being a [[contemporary R&B|R&B]], [[hip-hop]] and [[funk]] song. "This Time Around" is written in the [[time signature]] of common time.<ref name="sheet"/> The song is played in the key of F Major.<ref name="sheet"/> The track's [[tempo]] is moderate and it's metronome is 108 [[Tempo|beats per minute]].<ref name="sheet">{{cite web |url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0015823 |title=This Time Around - Michael Jackson Digital Sheet Music  (Digital Download) |work=MusicNotes.com |publisher=[[Alfred Publishing|Alfred Publishing Co. Inc]] |accessdate=2010-04-07}}</ref> The song has a basic sequence of Dm11<U+2013>Dm9 as its [[chord progression]].<ref name="sheet"/> "This Time Around"{{'}}s lyrics are about both musicians problems with being famous and stardom. On December 26, 1995, the track was released by [[Epic Records]] as a promotional single in the United States only. The promo was formatted in three different versions, which were as a stand alone CD single with just the song, as a 12" single with remixes and as a [[maxi-single]] with remixes.

==Release and reception==
James Hunter of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' described it as a "dynamite jam...done with Atlanta R&B hotshot [[Dallas Austin]] that's ripe for remixes".<ref name="RS HIStory">{{cite news|first=James |last=Hunter |url=http://www.rollingstone.com/artists/michaeljackson/albums/album/312830/review/5943497/history_past_present_and_future_book_1
 |title=Michael Jackson HIStory |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=1995-08-10 |accessdate=2008-07-23}}</ref> Jon Pareles of ''[[The New York Times]]'' believed that Jackson "muttered" lyrics such as "They thought they really had control of me".<ref name="HIStory review NYT">{{cite web |first=Jon |last=Pareles |url=http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=990CE0DD123DF93BA25755C0A963958260&scp=4&sq=HIStory+album+michael+jackson+review&st=nyt
 |title=Pop View; Michael Jackson Is Angry, Understand? |publisher=''The New York Times'' |date=1995-06-18 |accessdate=2008-09-18 }}</ref> 

Although "This Time Around" did not chart on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], the track had a good chart performance on music component charts in the United States. The song charted on music charts based solely on radio airplay throughout the country. "This Time Around" charted within the top forty, peaking at number thirty-six, on the ''Billboard'' Rhythmic Top 40 music chart in 1995.<ref name="charts">{{cite web |url=http://www.allmusic.com/cg/amg.dll?p=amg&sql=10:j9fixq95ld6e~T3 |title=allmusic ((( Got to be There > Charts & Awards > Billboard Singles ))) |work=Allmusic |publisher=Rovi Corporation |accessdate=2010-04-08}}</ref> The song peaked at number eighteen on the ''Billboard'' Dance Music/Club Play Singles  music charts 1996, respectively.<ref name="charts"/> In 1996, the track also peaked at number twenty-three on the ''Billboard'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] chart.<ref name="nelsongeorgecharts">*[[Nelson George|George, Nelson]] (2004). ''[[Michael Jackson: The Ultimate Collection]]'' booklet p, 48. [[Sony BMG]].</ref>

